Class Subnet<IP extends IPAddress<IP>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.robtimus.net.ip.AbstractIPRange<IP>
      • com.github.robtimus.net.ip.Subnet<IP>
  • Type Parameters:
    IP - The type of IP address in the subnet.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPRange<IP>, Iterable<IP>, Collection<IP>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    IPv4Subnet, IPv6Subnet

    public abstract class Subnet<IP extends IPAddress<IP>>
extends AbstractIPRange<IP>
    Represents a subnet of IP addresses. Immutable.
    Author:
    Rob Spoor

      • valueOf

        public static Subnet<?> valueOf(IPAddress<?> routingPrefix,
                                int prefixLength)
        Returns a subnet represented by a routing prefix and a prefix length. The given routing prefix must be the start of the subnet of the given prefix length that contains the routing prefix. For example, 192.168.0.0 is valid for prefix length 16, but 192.168.0.1 is not.
        Parameters:
        routingPrefix - The routing prefix of the subnet.
        prefixLength - The length of the prefix of the subnet.
        Returns:
        A subnet represented by the given routing prefix and prefix length.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given routing prefix is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given prefix length is not valid for the IP address, or if the given routing prefix is not the start of the subnet of the given prefix length that contains the routing prefix.

      • valueOf

        public static Subnet<?> valueOf(CharSequence routingPrefix,
                                int prefixLength)
        Returns a subnet represented by a routing prefix and a prefix length. The given routing prefix must be the start of the subnet of the given prefix length that contains the routing prefix. For example, 192.168.0.0 is valid for prefix length 16, but 192.168.0.1 is not.
        Parameters:
        routingPrefix - The routing prefix of the subnet.
        prefixLength - The length of the prefix of the subnet.
        Returns:
        A subnet represented by the given routing prefix and prefix length.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given routing prefix is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given routing prefix does not represent a valid IP address, or if the given prefix length is not valid for the IP address, or if the given routing prefix is not the start of the subnet of the given prefix length that contains the routing prefix.
        See Also:
        valueOf(IPAddress, int)
